description._content: Catalog #: 09_01608 Title: First Lieutenant Harry Haw Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Curtiss JN-4D ""Jenny"" aircraft after a crash. Handwritten inscription ""Doc says 'Lets splice the wings and be up and at'em"", Harry Haw served in the U.S. Army in the 514th Observation Squadron. He entered the U.S. Army in 1917 and became a First Lieutenant in 1930. He became a civilian Transport Pilot by 1930 and had logged 789 flying hours by 1934. he later became Principal of the Alice Birney school.
